\begin_layout Proof
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
hyperref[prop:sigmaAlgebraGeneratedbyLisBorel]{Recall}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 that the collection of half-open intervals 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{L}=\left\{ \left(a,b\right]\mid-\infty<a\leq b<\infty\right\} $
\end_inset

 is a generating class for 
\begin_inset Formula $\borel\left(\R\right).$
\end_inset

 Observe that for any 
\begin_inset Formula $a\leq b\in\R$
\end_inset

,
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\left(a,b\right]=\bigcap_{n\in\N}\left(\left(a,\infty\right)\cap\left(b+\frac{1}{n},\infty\right)\right)
\]

\end_inset

and so 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{L}\subseteq\sigma\left(\left\{ \left(a,\infty\right)\mid\forall a\in\R\right\} \right)$
